strictly adhere with the provisions of RA No. 6713, EO 77, COA Circular No. 77-61 and COA Circular No. 2012-003.

The Audit Team recommended that the Management to:

direct both the Municipal Budget Officer and the Municipal Planning and Development Officer to refrain from allowing lump-sum appropriations under its 20% Development Fund instead require each recipient to provide specific and allowable developmental projects corresponding to the amount in the budget;

require Municipal Engineer and Municipal Planning and Development Officer to undertake the effective and efficient implementation of the proposed projects within their targeted completion period;

review unimplemented PPAs to ascertain viability of their implementation otherwise reprogram for a more viable and significant PPAs in accordance to the socio-economic development and environmental management requirements provided under Section 287 of Republic Act No. 7160 and DILG and DBM  JMC No. 2017-1.

The Audit Team recommended that the Management:

require the MDRRMO to maximize utilization of its DRRM Funds by accelerating the implementation/acquisition of the needed disaster and rescue equipment specifically funded for disaster preparedness, response, rehabilitation and recovery in order to improve the capacity of the Municipality to respond to emergencies or disaster;

convene with the MDRRM Council to review and evaluate planned PPAs, identify and address the delay of implementation and ensure that identified PPAs are viable for immediate implementation

